C# is one of the Most Popular Language and C# is developed by Microsoft which will be Work on.NET FrameWork
By using c# we can Develop the Web Apps and Windows and Games etc.....
Why we use c# Because c# is an OOPS which gives a clear structure to programs and allows code to be reused.
c# is also Similar to c++ c and java.....

#sample Program//

using System;

namespace HelloWorld
{
  class Program
  {
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
      Console.WriteLine("Hello World!");    
    }
  }
}

1.Using system-Means we can use the classes from the system namespace.
2.namespace means to organize the code and it is the container for the classes.
3.class is a container for data and methods, which brings functionality to your program. Every line of code that runs in C# must be inside a class.
4.Main method Any code inside its curly brackets {} will be executed.
5.using System line, you would have to write System.Console.WriteLine()
